<br>
There are no plans to nerf Fading Memories as it applies to current content.  There is the possibility of adding NPCs in the future who are more difficult to fade from, or possibly immune, but you won't see any chance to how FM currently works.<br>
<br>
Thanks to everyone who took the time to attend the summit and provide feedback.  It definitely helped us create and continue to solidify a list of priorities for EQ.<br>
<br>
-Ryan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wystlertwystler>Wystler Twystler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#330000>(6/7/04 1:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=67>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letter from SoE from Summit</span><hr size=1> On Fade changes, <br>
